title: My Clique
description: Chloe, a child prodigy, finds it difficult to connect with her much older classmates. The Bears take her under their wing and show her how to make great college friends.
seriesname: Asian American and Pacific Islander Heritage Month

title: Flyaway
description: When Adorabat's spirit transcends her body during a meditation exercise, Mao Mao and Badgerclops have to figure out a way to return her to the real world.
seriesname: Asian American and Pacific Islander Heritage Month

title: Lucky Ducky Mug
description: When Adorabat and Badgerclops break Mao Mao's favorite mug, he gives them the silent treatment.
seriesname: Asian American and Pacific Islander Heritage Month

title: Head Chef
description: Mao Mao faces off with Badgerclops in a competition to determine whether cooking (and being a hero) is an art or a science.
seriesname: Asian American and Pacific Islander Heritage Month

title: Breakup
description:
Feeling left out, Adorabat wishes Mao Mao and Badgerclops would spend less time with each other and more time with her. When she gets
what she wishes for and accidentally breaks up their friendship, only the secret of their past can bring them back together.
seriesname: Asian American and Pacific Islander Heritage Month

title: The Truth Stinks
description: Badgerclops smells, but Mao Mao and Adorabat don't know how to tell him.
seriesname: Asian American and Pacific Islander Heritage Month

title: Mao Mao's Bike Adventure
description: When Mao Mao underestimates enemy and friend alike, it almost costs him the entire kingdom.
seriesname: Asian American and Pacific Islander Heritage Month

title: Rose Buds
description: Steven gets a surprise visit from some old friends, and an even more surprising introduction to some new ones.
seriesname: Asian American and Pacific Islander Heritage Month

title: Zing Your Heart Out
description: When Adorabat starts to aggressively heckle everyone with her new zing power, she threatens the entire kingdom.
seriesname: Asian American and Pacific Islander Heritage Month

title: Everything's Fine
description: Steven insists that everything is fine.
seriesname: Asian American and Pacific Islander Heritage Month

title: Orangusnake Begins
description: Mao Mao goads Orangusnake and the Sky Pirates into becoming truly terrible villains worthy of a legendary hero such as himself.
seriesname: Asian American and Pacific Islander Heritage Month

title: Together Forever
description: Connie has a really clear vision for her future. Steven wants to make sure he'll be a part of it.
seriesname: Asian American and Pacific Islander Heritage Month

title: Crack the Whip
description: Amethyst is left in charge of Steven and Connie, and there will be no training while she's around!
seriesname: Asian American and Pacific Islander Heritage Month

title: Strange Bedfellows
description: After an insane battle, MM and OS end up in the same hospital room. But even in full body casts, the sworn enemies continue the fight.
seriesname: Asian American and Pacific Islander Heritage Month

title: Try Hard
description: When the Sky Pirates take Mao Mao and Badgerclops hostage, it's up to Adorabat to save the day.
seriesname: Asian American and Pacific Islander Heritage Month

title: Weapon of Choice
description: Worried that his sword is a glorified consolation prize, Mao Mao sets out to prove the worth of his weapon.
seriesname: Asian American and Pacific Islander Heritage Month

title: The Demon
description: Chloe and Ice Bear accidentally lose Chloe's prized hoodie to the ferocious dog next store. They go on a mission to get it back.
seriesname: Asian American and Pacific Islander Heritage Month

title: Bobo Chan
description: Badgerclops adopts an abandoned monster, but some things are better left in the wild.
seriesname: Asian American and Pacific Islander Heritage Month

title: Fusion Cuisine
description: In an effort to win over Connie's parents, Steven convinces the Gems to fuse together and pretend to be his mother.
seriesname: Asian American and Pacific Islander Heritage Month

title: Small
description: Mao Mao's legendary, gigantic and critical father visits his son at his new job as sheriff.
seriesname: Asian American and Pacific Islander Heritage Month

title: I Am My Monster
description: Everything is not fine.
seriesname: Asian American and Pacific Islander Heritage Month

title: Chloe and Ice Bear
description: On a day out with just Ice Bear, Chloe realizes Ice Bear only runs errands for his brothers. Determined to show him a fun day in the city, Chloe promises to help Ice Bear have a good time, even if it means staying  in a museum after it closes.
seriesname: Asian American and Pacific Islander Heritage Month

title: Meet Tanya Keys
description: When bounty hunter Tanya Keys comes to town for Badgerclops, it's up to Mao Mao and Adorabat to save their friend -- even if he's been on the wrong side of the law.
seriesname: Asian American and Pacific Islander Heritage Month

title: Hurricane Hal
description: A storm rolls in while the Bears are separated. Grizz looks after the Poppy Rangers. Panda is stuck with Charlie in his car. And Chloe and Ice Bear are in the city seeking a ride home.
seriesname: Asian American and Pacific Islander Heritage Month

title: Slumber Party
description: A thunderstorm forces Chloe to spend the night at the Cave with the Bears. When Chloe's parents tell the Bears to protect Chloe, they take the task a bit too seriously.
seriesname: Asian American and Pacific Islander Heritage Month

title: Growing Pains
description: Steven visits a doctor for the first time.
seriesname: Asian American and Pacific Islander Heritage Month

title: Road Trip
description: Chloe and the Bears take a road trip to see a meteor shower. Ice Bear, the only one licensed to drive, is put in charge, which becomes harder than he thought.
seriesname: Asian American and Pacific Islander Heritage Month

title: Enemy Mime
description: When the Sheriff's Dept fights a monster that copies their every move, they'll have to find a way to fight without fighting.
seriesname: Asian American and Pacific Islander Heritage Month

title: Lonely Kid
description: When AD has trouble making friends at school, MM tells her the story of how he made his first real friend —BB.
seriesname: Asian American and Pacific Islander Heritage Month

title: Fright Wig
description: When the King cannot overcome his fears, he abuses having the Sheriff's Dept. on call.
seriesname: Asian American and Pacific Islander Heritage Month

title: Captured Clops
description: Badgerclops is tired of his responsibilities at Sheriff's HQ, so he joins the Sky Pirates.
seriesname: Asian American and Pacific Islander Heritage Month

title: Professor Lampwick
description: Chloe's professor is too mean to give her any face time to talk over her poor grade. The Bears take things into their own hands to help, causing big trouble for Chloe.
seriesname: Asian American and Pacific Islander Heritage Month

title: Thumb War
description: The gang decide to compete in the annual Thumb War competition, but a surprise forces Mao Mao to deal with the unthinkable... losing.
seriesname: Asian American and Pacific Islander Heritage Month

title: Scared of Puppets
description: Mao Mao is scared of puppets.
seriesname: Asian American and Pacific Islander Heritage Month

title: All By Mao Self
description: Mao Mao's desire to be a legend drives him to keep topping himself. But how much is enough?
seriesname: Asian American and Pacific Islander Heritage Month

title: Ultraclops
description: Badgerclops gets huge to destroy a towering monster, but when he refuses to shrink down, the kingdom faces a new terror.
seriesname: Asian American and Pacific Islander Heritage Month

title: Legend of Torbaclaun
description: When the Sweetypies think the mythical Torbaclaun has come to Pure Heart Valley, Mao Mao tries to prove to them that it isn't real.
seriesname: Asian American and Pacific Islander Heritage Month

title: Baost in Show
description: When Bao Bao returns, and the King makes him his pet, Mao Mao must rescue his ex-partner.
seriesname: Asian American and Pacific Islander Heritage Month

title: Everyone's Tube
description: Through a standard video browsing session online, we get a glimpse of the different kinds of videos the Bears have posted.
seriesname: Asian American and Pacific Islander Heritage Month

title: Outfoxed
description: When Rufus and Reg come to swindle the town, Sheriff Mao Mao teaches them a lesson in justice.
seriesname: Asian American and Pacific Islander Heritage Month

title: Badge-a-fire Explosion
description: When BC comes out of a rare state of hyper-focused creativity, he may have made something that could destroy all of PHV.
seriesname: Asian American and Pacific Islander Heritage Month

title: Storm in the Room
description: Steven goes into his room in the temple to look for answers.
seriesname: Asian American and Pacific Islander Heritage Month

title: Not Impressed
description: When a Sweetypie isn't impressed with the sheriff dept's antics, our three heroes try everything to win him over.
seriesname: Asian American and Pacific Islander Heritage Month

title: Sleeper Sofa
description: When the Sky Pirates infiltrate Sheriff HQ, they put our heroes in danger!
seriesname: Asian American and Pacific Islander Heritage Month

title: The Perfect Adventure
description: When Mao Mao gets hungry for the perfect adventure, Adorabat tells a white lie.
seriesname: Asian American and Pacific Islander Heritage Month

title: The Future
description: Steven is finally ready to move on.
seriesname: Asian American and Pacific Islander Heritage Month

title: The Perfect Couple
description: When Mao Mao accidentally breaks up the most perfect couple in Pure Heart Valley, he has to figure out how to get them back together.
seriesname: Asian American and Pacific Islander Heritage Month

title: He's the Sheriff
description: The gang struggles to get rid of the King when he joins them as their new deputy-for-a-day!
seriesname: Asian American and Pacific Islander Heritage Month

title: Bismuth Casual
description: Pearl invites Bismuth to the roller rink for a lesson on how to forge human relationships.
seriesname: Asian American and Pacific Islander Heritage Month

title: Sick Mao
description: When Mao Mao won't admit that he's sick, he puts the town in danger.
seriesname: Asian American and Pacific Islander Heritage Month

title: Sugar Berry Fever
description: Mao Mao tries to hide his love of cobbler.
seriesname: Asian American and Pacific Islander Heritage Month

title: Chloe
description: Chloe spends time with the Bears in an effort to research them for an upcoming presentation. But when the Bears sneak a peek at her very dry report, the Bears decide to jazz it up with exaggerated facts about themselves and their lifestyle.
seriesname: Asian American and Pacific Islander Heritage Month

title: Prickly Pair
description: After leaving Little Homeschool, Steven has found a new hobby, plants.
seriesname: Asian American and Pacific Islander Heritage Month

title: Sworn to the Sword
description: Connie trains with Pearl to be a swordfighter.
seriesname: Asian American and Pacific Islander Heritage Month

title: Trading Day
description: When they think each others' lives are easier, the heroes switch roles.
seriesname: Asian American and Pacific Islander Heritage Month

title: The Library
description: The Bears find Chloe in the library exhausted from studying for an exam all day. The Bears stay to help Chloe study but make things worse in the process.
seriesname: Asian American and Pacific Islander Heritage Month

title: Alone Together
description: The Gems try to teach Steven to use his fusion powers.
seriesname: Asian American and Pacific Islander Heritage Month

title: Adoradad
description: When AD's dad forbids her from working with the Sheriff's Dept because it's too dangerous, AD sets out to prove that she can take care of herself.
seriesname: Asian American and Pacific Islander Heritage Month

title: Bao Bao's Revenge
description: When Mao Mao's old partner threatens the kingdom, his friends will need to learn about his past in order to protect the present.
seriesname: Asian American and Pacific Islander Heritage Month

title: Mao Mao's Nakey
description: When MM loses his clothes while trying to scale the Ruby Pure Heart, he has to get back to Sheriff's HQ by daybreak.
seriesname: Asian American and Pacific Islander Heritage Month

title: I Love You Mao Mao
description: An explosive loner and his slacker best friend are waylaid from their journey into legend, only to find that their story is just beginning.
seriesname: Asian American and Pacific Islander Heritage Month

title: No Shortcuts
description: After struggling to keep up, Adorabat gets a cybernetic "Mega-Mech." But can fancy new powers make up for experience?
seriesname: Asian American and Pacific Islander Heritage Month

title: Snow Day
description: Steven and the Crystal Gems get a chance to catch up when they're all snowed in together.
seriesname: Asian American and Pacific Islander Heritage Month
